<doc id="1086414" wikidata="Q3533570" url="?curid=1086414" title="Democratic People's Front">
<text>The Western People&#x27;s Front, currently named the Democratic People&#x27;s Front (; &quot;Prajathanthravadi Janatha Peramunay&quot;), is a political party in Sri Lanka active in the Western Province. 

WPF was originally a trade union, which then became a political party under the leadership of Mano Ganesan. It draws most of its support from the Tamil population of Colombo.

