<doc id="1086656" wikidata="Q7688955" url="?curid=1086656" title="Taut submanifold">
<text>In mathematics, a (compact) taut submanifold &quot;N&quot; of a space form &quot;M&quot; is a compact submanifold with the property that for every formula_1 the distance function 

:formula_2

is a perfect Morse function.

If &quot;N&quot; is not compact, one needs to consider the restriction of the formula_3 to any of their sublevel sets.

